Roles & Responsibilities
This is a new role that will provide administrative support to the CEO office in the first instance. The CEO office has several staff which are responsible for supporting the CEO in realising the company vision, goals and objectives. This role is pivotal to the effective operational delivery of the CEOs office and will be an excellent opportunity for someone seeking to gain exposure into a varied and hospitable corporate culture.


This role will provide direct administrative support to the Head, Operations / CIO as well as CEO’s Executive Assistant (EA) in the first instance, which will subsequently develop wider opportunities depending on the willingness to engage and undertake additional duties as the candidate matures.

Responsibilities

Administrative support:
Assist in recording of meeting minutes, action items, preparation of presentations, report writing and generation, excel sheets and reporting, task scheduling, as part of general business;
Maintain documents, reports, records including filing of all associated to the office standards;
Communicate and liaise with relevant departments as directed by Head, Ops / EA;
Upon training of DP’s ERP, enter and manage data including the preparation of any Purchase Orders for processing;
Assist in the preparation of client gifts during festive occasions;
Provide logistics support for office events and workshops, including organising and coordination.

Time management:
Assist in organising appointments, meetings, and providing administrative support to project and corporate business teams;
As part of appointment and meetings, to coordinate room reservations including any audio-visual activities with ICT, and any specific refreshments before meeting commencement;
Assist with the coordination of the CEOs driver scheduling.

Qualifications
Bachelor's degree or equivalent experience, fresh graduates are encouraged to apply;
Proficient in Microsoft Office suite;
Strong organisational aptitude including demonstrable time management skills, people interaction;
Excellent communication skills in both written and spoken English;
A flexible and adaptable approach to work;
Self-motivated and diligent;
Energetic and enthusiastic to learn.
